<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 2:37PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Heard
and northwestern Troup Counties through 300 PM EDT...
At 237 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Glenn, or 8 miles
southwest of Franklin, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Franklin, Waresville, Glenn and Texas.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
